#. <section class="sutta" id="an5.166"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an5.166:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 5"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 5"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.166:0.2"
msgid "17. Āghātavagga"
msgstr "17. Resentment"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an5.166:0.3"
msgid "166. Nirodhasutta"
msgstr "166. Cessation"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
#. VAR: samāpajjeyyāpi vuṭṭhaheyyāpi → samāpajjeyyapi vuṭṭhaheyyapi (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "an5.166:1.1"
msgid ""
"Tatra kho āyasmā sāriputto bhikkhū āmantesi … pe … “idhāvuso, bhikkhu "
"sīlasampanno samādhisampanno paññāsampanno saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ "
"samāpajjeyyāpi vuṭṭhaheyyāpi—"
msgstr ""
"There Venerable Sāriputta addressed the mendicants: … “Reverends, take a "
"mendicant who is accomplished in ethics, immersion, and wisdom. They might "
"enter into and emerge from the cessation of perception and feeling."

msgctxt "an5.166:1.2"
msgid "atthetaṃ ṭhānaṃ."
msgstr "That is possible."

# The phrase manomayaṃ kāyaṃ upapanno is difficult. manomayaṃ kāyaṃ normally means “mind-made body”, but kāyaṃ upapanno means “reborn in a order (of gods), i.e. realm.” BB translates inconsistently, using “group of mind-made [deities]” here, but “in a mind-made body” at AN 11.13.
#. VAR: kabaḷīkārāhārabhakkhānaṃ → kabaḷiṃkārāhārabhakkhānaṃ (bj, s1, km, pts1) | kabaliṃ kārāhārabhakkhānaṃ (s2, s3)
msgctxt "an5.166:1.3"
msgid ""
"No ce diṭṭheva dhamme aññaṃ ārādheyya, atikkammeva kabaḷīkārāhārabhakkhānaṃ "
"devānaṃ sahabyataṃ aññataraṃ manomayaṃ kāyaṃ upapanno saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ "
"samāpajjeyyāpi vuṭṭhaheyyāpi—"
msgstr ""
"If they don’t reach enlightenment in this very life, then, surpassing the "
"company of gods that consume solid food, they’re reborn in a certain group "
"of mind-made gods. There they might enter into and emerge from the cessation "
"of perception and feeling."

msgctxt "an5.166:1.4"
msgid "atthetaṃ ṭhānan”ti."
msgstr "That is possible.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an5.166:2.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, āyasmā udāyī āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "When he said this, Venerable Udāyī said to him:"

msgctxt "an5.166:2.2"
msgid ""
"“aṭṭhānaṃ kho etaṃ, āvuso sāriputta, anavakāso yaṃ so bhikkhu atikkammeva "
"kabaḷīkārāhārabhakkhānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ aññataraṃ manomayaṃ kāyaṃ "
"upapanno saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ samāpajjeyyāpi vuṭṭhaheyyāpi—"
msgstr "“This is not possible, Reverend Sāriputta, it cannot happen!”"

msgctxt "an5.166:2.3"
msgid "natthetaṃ ṭhānan”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.193"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an5.166:3.1"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho … pe … tatiyampi kho āyasmā sāriputto bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "But for a second … and a third time Sāriputta repeated his statement."

msgctxt "an5.166:3.2"
msgid ""
"“idhāvuso, bhikkhu sīlasampanno samādhisampanno paññāsampanno "
"saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ samāpajjeyyāpi vuṭṭhaheyyāpi—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an5.166:3.3"
msgid "atthetaṃ ṭhānaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an5.166:3.4"
msgid ""
"No ce diṭṭheva dhamme aññaṃ ārādheyya, atikkammeva kabaḷīkārāhārabhakkhānaṃ "
"devānaṃ sahabyataṃ aññataraṃ manomayaṃ kāyaṃ upapanno saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ "
"samāpajjeyyāpi vuṭṭhaheyyāpi—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an5.166:3.5"
msgid "atthetaṃ ṭhānan”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an5.166:4.1"
msgid "Tatiyampi kho āyasmā udāyī āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "And for a third time, Udāyī said to him:"

msgctxt "an5.166:4.2"
msgid ""
"“aṭṭhānaṃ kho etaṃ, āvuso sāriputta, anavakāso yaṃ so bhikkhu atikkammeva "
"kabaḷīkārāhārabhakkhānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ aññataraṃ manomayaṃ kāyaṃ "
"upapanno saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ samāpajjeyyāpi vuṭṭhaheyyāpi—"
msgstr "“This is not possible, Reverend Sāriputta, it cannot happen!”"

msgctxt "an5.166:4.3"
msgid "natthetaṃ ṭhānan”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an5.166:5.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmato sāriputtassa etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then Venerable Sāriputta thought:"

#. VAR: yāvatatiyakampi → yāvatatiyampi (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "an5.166:5.2"
msgid ""
"“yāvatatiyakampi kho me āyasmā udāyī paṭikkosati, na ca me koci bhikkhu "
"anumodati."
msgstr ""
"“Venerable Udāyī disagrees with me three times, and not one mendicant agrees "
"with me."

msgctxt "an5.166:5.3"
msgid "Yannūnāhaṃ yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkameyyan”ti."
msgstr "Why don’t I go to see the Buddha?”"

msgctxt "an5.166:5.4"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā sāriputto yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā "
"bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi."
msgstr "Then Sāriputta went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side,"

msgctxt "an5.166:5.5"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā sāriputto bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "and said to the mendicants:"

msgctxt "an5.166:5.6"
msgid ""
"“idhāvuso, bhikkhu sīlasampanno samādhisampanno paññāsampanno "
"saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ samāpajjeyyāpi vuṭṭhaheyyāpi—"
msgstr ""
"“Reverends, take a mendicant who is accomplished in ethics, immersion, and "
"wisdom. They might enter into and emerge from the cessation of perception "
"and feeling."

msgctxt "an5.166:5.7"
msgid "atthetaṃ ṭhānaṃ."
msgstr "There is such a possibility."

msgctxt "an5.166:5.8"
msgid ""
"No ce diṭṭheva dhamme aññaṃ ārādheyya, atikkammeva kabaḷīkārāhārabhakkhānaṃ "
"devānaṃ sahabyataṃ aññataraṃ manomayaṃ kāyaṃ upapanno saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ "
"samāpajjeyyāpi vuṭṭhaheyyāpi—"
msgstr ""
"If they don’t reach enlightenment in this very life, they’re reborn in the "
"company of a certain group of mind-made gods, who surpass the gods that "
"consume solid food. There they might enter into and emerge from the "
"cessation of perception and feeling."

msgctxt "an5.166:5.9"
msgid "atthetaṃ ṭhānan”ti."
msgstr "That is possible.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an5.166:6.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, āyasmā udāyī āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "When he said this, Udāyī said to him:"

msgctxt "an5.166:6.2"
msgid ""
"“aṭṭhānaṃ kho etaṃ, āvuso sāriputta, anavakāso yaṃ so bhikkhu atikkammeva "
"kabaḷīkārāhārabhakkhānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ aññataraṃ manomayaṃ kāyaṃ "
"upapanno saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ samāpajjeyyāpi vuṭṭhaheyyāpi—"
msgstr "“This is not possible, Reverend Sāriputta, it cannot happen!”"

msgctxt "an5.166:6.3"
msgid "natthetaṃ ṭhānan”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.194"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "an5.166:7.1"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho … pe … tatiyampi kho āyasmā sāriputto bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "But for a second … and a third time Sāriputta repeated his statement."

msgctxt "an5.166:7.2"
msgid ""
"“idhāvuso, bhikkhu sīlasampanno samādhisampanno paññāsampanno "
"saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ samāpajjeyyāpi vuṭṭhaheyyāpi—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an5.166:7.3"
msgid "atthetaṃ ṭhānaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an5.166:7.4"
msgid ""
"No ce diṭṭheva dhamme aññaṃ ārādheyya, atikkammeva kabaḷīkārāhārabhakkhānaṃ "
"devānaṃ sahabyataṃ aññataraṃ manomayaṃ kāyaṃ upapanno saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ "
"samāpajjeyyāpi vuṭṭhaheyyāpi—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an5.166:7.5"
msgid "atthetaṃ ṭhānan”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "an5.166:8.1"
msgid "Tatiyampi kho āyasmā udāyī āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "And for a third time, Udāyī said to him:"

msgctxt "an5.166:8.2"
msgid ""
"“aṭṭhānaṃ kho etaṃ, āvuso sāriputta, anavakāso yaṃ so bhikkhu atikkammeva "
"kabaḷīkārāhārabhakkhānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ aññataraṃ manomayaṃ kāyaṃ "
"upapanno saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ samāpajjeyyāpi vuṭṭhaheyyāpi—"
msgstr "“This is not possible, Reverend Sāriputta, it cannot happen!”"

msgctxt "an5.166:8.3"
msgid "natthetaṃ ṭhānan”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "an5.166:9.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmato sāriputtassa etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then Venerable Sāriputta thought:"

msgctxt "an5.166:9.2"
msgid ""
"“bhagavatopi kho me sammukhā āyasmā udāyī yāvatatiyakaṃ paṭikkosati, na ca "
"me koci bhikkhu anumodati."
msgstr ""
"“Even in front of the Buddha Venerable Udāyī disagrees with me three times, "
"and not one mendicant agrees with me."

msgctxt "an5.166:9.3"
msgid "Yannūnāhaṃ tuṇhī assan”ti."
msgstr "I’d better stay silent.”"

msgctxt "an5.166:9.4"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā sāriputto tuṇhī ahosi."
msgstr "Then Sāriputta fell silent."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "an5.166:10.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ udāyiṃ āmantesi:"
msgstr "Then the Buddha said to Venerable Udāyī:"

msgctxt "an5.166:10.2"
msgid "“kaṃ pana tvaṃ, udāyi, manomayaṃ kāyaṃ paccesī”ti?"
msgstr "“But Udāyī, do you believe in a mind-made body?”"

msgctxt "an5.166:10.3"
msgid "“Ye te, bhante, devā arūpino saññāmayā”ti."
msgstr "“Those gods, sir, who are formless, made of perception.”"

msgctxt "an5.166:10.4"
msgid "“Kiṃ nu kho tuyhaṃ, udāyi, bālassa abyattassa bhaṇitena."
msgstr "“Udāyī, what has an incompetent fool like you got to say?"

msgctxt "an5.166:10.5"
msgid "Tvampi nāma bhaṇitabbaṃ maññasī”ti."
msgstr "How on earth could you imagine you’ve got something worth saying!”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "an5.166:11.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ āmantesi:"
msgstr "Then the Buddha said to Venerable Ānanda:"

msgctxt "an5.166:11.2"
msgid "“atthi nāma, ānanda, theraṃ bhikkhuṃ vihesiyamānaṃ ajjhupekkhissatha."
msgstr ""
"“Ānanda! There’s a senior mendicant being harassed, and you just watch it "
"happening."

#. VAR: theramhi → byattamhi (s1-3, km, mr)
msgctxt "an5.166:11.3"
msgid ""
"Na hi nāma, ānanda, kāruññampi bhavissati theramhi bhikkhumhi "
"vihesiyamānamhī”ti."
msgstr ""
"Don’t you have any compassion for a senior mendicant who is being harassed?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
msgctxt "an5.166:12.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "Then the Buddha addressed the mendicants:"

msgctxt "an5.166:12.2"
msgid ""
"“idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sīlasampanno samādhisampanno paññāsampanno "
"saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ samāpajjeyyāpi vuṭṭhaheyyāpi—"
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, take a mendicant who is accomplished in ethics, immersion, and "
"wisdom. They might enter into and emerge from the cessation of perception "
"and feeling."

msgctxt "an5.166:12.3"
msgid "atthetaṃ ṭhānaṃ."
msgstr "That is possible."

msgctxt "an5.166:12.4"
msgid ""
"No ce diṭṭheva dhamme aññaṃ ārādheyya, atikkammeva kabaḷīkārāhārabhakkhānaṃ "
"devānaṃ sahabyataṃ aññataraṃ manomayaṃ kāyaṃ upapanno saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ "
"samāpajjeyyāpi vuṭṭhaheyyāpi—"
msgstr ""
"If they don’t reach enlightenment in this very life, they’re reborn in the "
"company of a certain group of mind-made gods, who surpass the gods that "
"consume solid food. There they might enter into and emerge from the "
"cessation of perception and feeling."

msgctxt "an5.166:12.5"
msgid "atthetaṃ ṭhānan”ti."
msgstr "That is possible.”"

msgctxt "an5.166:12.6"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā."
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said."

msgctxt "an5.166:12.7"
msgid "Idaṃ vatvāna sugato uṭṭhāyāsanā vihāraṃ pāvisi."
msgstr ""
"When he had spoken, the Holy One got up from his seat and entered his "
"dwelling."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.195"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
msgctxt "an5.166:13.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā ānando acirapakkantassa bhagavato yenāyasmā upavāṇo "
"tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ upavāṇaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then, not long after the Buddha had left, Venerable Ānanda went to Venerable "
"Upavāṇa and said to him:"

msgctxt "an5.166:13.2"
msgid "“idhāvuso upavāṇa, aññe there bhikkhū vihesenti."
msgstr "“Reverend Upavāṇa, they’ve been harassing other senior mendicants,"

# reading pucchama, see BB.
msgctxt "an5.166:13.3"
msgid "Mayaṃ tena na muccāma."
msgstr "but I didn’t question them."

msgctxt "an5.166:13.4"
msgid ""
"Anacchariyaṃ kho, panetaṃ āvuso upavāṇa, yaṃ bhagavā sāyanhasamayaṃ "
"paṭisallānā vuṭṭhito etadeva ārabbha udāhareyya yathā āyasmantaṃyevettha "
"upavāṇaṃ paṭibhāseyya."
msgstr ""
"I wouldn’t be surprised if the Buddha makes a statement about this when he "
"comes out of retreat later this afternoon. He might even call upon Venerable "
"Upavāṇa himself."

msgctxt "an5.166:13.5"
msgid "Idāneva amhākaṃ sārajjaṃ okkantan”ti."
msgstr "And right now I feel timid.”"

msgctxt "an5.166:13.6"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā sāyanhasamayaṃ paṭisallānā vuṭṭhito yena upaṭṭhānasālā "
"tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi. Nisajja kho bhagavā "
"āyasmantaṃ upavāṇaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then in the late afternoon, the Buddha came out of retreat and went to the "
"assembly hall, where he sat on the seat spread out, and said to Upavāṇa:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc14"></a>
msgctxt "an5.166:14.1"
msgid ""
"“Katihi nu kho, upavāṇa, dhammehi samannāgato thero bhikkhu sabrahmacārīnaṃ "
"piyo ca hoti manāpo ca garu ca bhāvanīyo cā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Upavāṇa, how many qualities should a senior mendicant have to be dear and "
"beloved to their spiritual companions, respected and admired?”"

msgctxt "an5.166:14.2"
msgid ""
"“Pañcahi, bhante, dhammehi samannāgato thero bhikkhu sabrahmacārīnaṃ piyo ca "
"hoti manāpo ca garu ca bhāvanīyo ca."
msgstr ""
"“Sir, a senior mendicant with five qualities is dear and beloved to their "
"spiritual companions, respected and admired."

msgctxt "an5.166:14.3"
msgid "Katamehi pañcahi?"
msgstr "What five?"

msgctxt "an5.166:14.4"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhante, thero bhikkhu sīlavā hoti … pe … samādāya sikkhati "
"sikkhāpadesu;"
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant is ethical, restrained in the code of conduct, and has "
"appropriate behavior and means of collecting alms. Seeing danger in the "
"slightest fault, they keep the rules they’ve undertaken."

msgctxt "an5.166:14.5"
msgid "bahussuto hoti … pe … diṭṭhiyā suppaṭividdhā;"
msgstr ""
"They’re very learned, remembering and keeping what they’ve learned. These "
"teachings are good in the beginning, good in the middle, and good in the "
"end, meaningful and well-phrased, describing a spiritual practice that’s "
"totally full and pure. They are very learned in such teachings, remembering "
"them, reciting them, mentally scrutinizing them, and understanding them with "
"right view."

#. VAR: anelagalāya → anelagaḷāya (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "an5.166:14.6"
msgid ""
"kalyāṇavāco hoti kalyāṇavākkaraṇo poriyā vācāya samannāgato vissaṭṭhāya "
"anelagalāya atthassa viññāpaniyā;"
msgstr ""
"They’re a good speaker, with a polished, clear, and articulate voice that "
"expresses the meaning."

msgctxt "an5.166:14.7"
msgid ""
"catunnaṃ jhānānaṃ ābhicetasikānaṃ diṭṭhadhammasukhavihārānaṃ nikāmalābhī "
"hoti akicchalābhī akasiralābhī;"
msgstr ""
"They get the four absorptions—blissful meditations in the present life that "
"belong to the higher mind—when they want, without trouble or difficulty."

msgctxt "an5.166:14.8"
msgid "āsavānaṃ khayā … pe … sacchikatvā upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"They realize the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this "
"very life. And they live having realized it with their own insight due to "
"the ending of defilements."

msgctxt "an5.166:14.9"
msgid ""
"Imehi kho, bhante, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato thero bhikkhu "
"sabrahmacārīnaṃ piyo ca hoti manāpo ca garu ca bhāvanīyo cā”ti."
msgstr ""
"A senior mendicant with these five qualities is dear and beloved to their "
"spiritual companions, respected and admired.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.196"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc15"></a>
msgctxt "an5.166:15.1"
msgid "“Sādhu sādhu, upavāṇa."
msgstr "“Good, good, Upavāṇa!"

msgctxt "an5.166:15.2"
msgid ""
"Imehi kho, upavāṇa, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato thero bhikkhu "
"sabrahmacārīnaṃ piyo ca hoti manāpo ca garu ca bhāvanīyo ca."
msgstr ""
"A senior mendicant with these five qualities is dear and beloved to their "
"spiritual companions, respected and admired."

msgctxt "an5.166:15.3"
msgid ""
"Ime ce, upavāṇa, pañca dhammā therassa bhikkhuno na saṃvijjeyyuṃ, taṃ "
"sabrahmacārī na sakkareyyuṃ na garuṃ kareyyuṃ na māneyyuṃ na pūjeyyuṃ "
"khaṇḍiccena pāliccena valittacatāya."
msgstr ""
"If these five qualities are not found in a senior mendicant, why would their "
"spiritual companions honor, respect, revere, or venerate them? Because of "
"their broken teeth, gray hair, and wrinkled skin?"

msgctxt "an5.166:15.4"
msgid ""
"Yasmā ca kho, upavāṇa, ime pañca dhammā therassa bhikkhuno saṃvijjanti, "
"tasmā taṃ sabrahmacārī sakkaronti garuṃ karonti mānenti pūjentī”ti."
msgstr ""
"But since these five qualities are found in a senior mendicant, their "
"spiritual companions honor, respect, revere, or venerate them.”"

